{
  "stem": "19969.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, not all of them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have one granddaughter who lives in Milwaukee-- --and one grandson who's now-- whose in the Army.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he'll be home this month and starting college right away.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All of my four children served in the military, but none of them cared for it very much.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They all spent one enlistment-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --either in the Army or in the Navy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Two of my grandsons, one spent enlistment in the Air Force.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He just graduated college this year.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The other one is in the Army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He'll be getting out this month.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He completes his four years and he'll be starting college.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So practically all of my-- all of my kids and part of my grandchildren have had some type of military service in either the Army, Navy, or Air Force.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But none of them cared for it and I didn't care for it, either, as a steady diet.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Although I spent eight years on active duty, I didn't want to make a career out of it, although I practically did because I got called back months after the end of World War II.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When I got so busy with my civilian occupation, I-- I was a director of natural resources for the state of Colorado for a while, the director of the State Water Conservation Board.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And so I was always busy, in-- in addition to my National Guard duties.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I had time to-- well, I had to-- to get promoted to brigadier general, I had to attend the Army War College at Fort Leavenworth, Kansas.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Well, it's called the Army Command and General Staff College at Fort Leavenworth; the Army War College at Carlisle, Pennsylvania; and the National War College at Fort McNair, Washington, DC.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
